{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645642","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645642"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:19:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:19:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18121"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18121","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18121"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.38,0.38,0.13,0.03,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10835"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80958"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10835","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10835"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18121"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66290"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4899"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6707"},{"type":"tags","id":"7322"},{"type":"tags","id":"7398"},{"type":"tags","id":"11436"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25214"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25217"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27591"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80958","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80958"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe cephalic vein is a superficial vein of the upper limb that is often used for venous access.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following anatomical structures does the cephalic vein pass through before joining the axillary vein?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Bicipital groove","Deltopectoral groove","Subscapular groove","Spiral groove","Intertubercular groove"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edeltopectoral groove\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct answer, as the cephalic vein passes through this groove between the deltoid and pectoralis major muscles before joining the axillary vein.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options refer to different anatomical structures:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBicipital groove\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eintertubercular groove\u003C/strong\u003E are the same structure - a groove between the greater and lesser tubercles of the humerus containing the long head of biceps tendon\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpiral groove\u003C/strong\u003E is located on the posterior humerus and contains the radial nerve and deep brachial artery\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubscapular groove\u003C/strong\u003E is not a recognised anatomical term\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The cephalic vein travels through the deltopectoral groove before joining the axillary vein.","The deltopectoral groove is located between the deltoid and pectoralis major muscles.","The cephalic vein is a superficial vein of the upper limb."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66290"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18121"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66290","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/66290"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-24T10:06:31+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-24T10:07:13+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10835"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80958"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4899","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4899"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Anatomy",